Philippines to Deploy " Mobile Tutors " in Remote Areas
MANILA , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- The Philippine government announced Sunday that it will deploy " mobile teachers " in remote areas to equip young indigenous folk and dwellers with the rudiments of reading , writing and arithmetic .
The Department of Education said that beginning next month , it will assign 300 mobile teachers to render teaching services , 40 hours weekly , in such faraway places as Palawan and the Cordillera Autonomous Region , in the Southwestern Philippines .
It said beneficiaries of the non-formal education program will be out-of-school youth aged 15 and above .
The mobile teachers with handy instructional aids will teach them the basics of reading , writing and computation as well as livelihood lessons , the department said .
The mobile teachers will hold sessions among residents of remote areas even if there are established elementary schools nearby , it added .
